name: Aegean
description: Native to the Greek islands known as the Cyclades in the Aegean Sea, these are natural cats, meaning they developed without humans getting involved in their breeding.

name: Abyssinian
description: The Abyssinian is one of the oldest known breeds of domesticated cat. These cats are known for their distinctive 'ticked' fur.

name: Siamese
description: Siamese cats are known for their sleek, elegant bodies, striking blue almond-shaped eyes, and short coats.

name: Bengal
description: Bengals are known for their wild, leopard-like appearance and active, playful nature.

name: Maine Coon
description: Maine Coons are one of the largest domesticated cat breeds and are known for their long fur and friendly personalities.

name: Ragdoll
description: Ragdolls are large, long-haired cats known for their docile and placid temperament, making them great companion pets.
